According to the country's new COVID-19 protocols, self-isolation period for those fully vaccinated and experiencing mild symptoms will be reduced to five days. For those who have been partially vaccinated or have not been vaccinated at all but are still asymptomatic or have mild symptoms, the self-isolation period will be seven days. All those people who test positive for COVID-19 and has moderate to severe symptoms, whether fully vaccinated or not, will be required to isolate for at least 10 days. The general population will no longer be subjected to contact tracing and quarantining. Health care workers may use their discretion to institute quarantine in exceptional cases, such as congregate settings prisons, boarding schools or vulnerable populations hospitalized patients, old age homes, Nyanga said. The country in southern Africa has a total of 261 913 confirmed cases, 256 438 recoveries, and 2 608 COVID-19-related deaths. --CGTN--